

Greek stocks ended higher on Monday, pushing the composite index to its highest closing since December 2000 on the Athens Stock Exchange, traders here said.

The index rose 0.58 percent to end at 3,442.20 points, with turnover an improved 244 million euros (287.7 million US dollars).

The FTSE/ASE 20 index for blue chip and heavily traded stocks rose 0.54 percent, while the FTSE/ASE MID 40 index and the FTSE/ ASE SmallCap 80 index rose 0.90 percent and 0.27 percent respectively.

Broadly, advancers led decliners by 143 to 133 with another 58 issues unchanged.

